</P>
<P>
   HKN-FLYERS-NEILSON (Philadelphia) _ The chemotherapy begins on
Monday. A doctor will cut the skin high on Roger Neilson's chest
and insert a small plastic device. Neilson's illness has sent a
worried chill through the National Hockey League this holiday
season. At age 65, coaching his seventh team, Neilson is the NHL's
favorite bachelor uncle, a little eccentric, a bit of a prince, one
of the elders of his craft with 23 seasons in the league. By Joe
Lapointe.
</P>
