<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    See you later, escalator
 &HT;    By Gregory Kallenberg
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Oh man, it's holiday time. And you know what
that means? Yes, there will be a crush of holiday shoppers. Yes,
there will be a plethora of mall workers pushing free sampples of
products you wouldn't buy if they paid you. Above all that, the
most annoying aspect of the holiday season is that there will be
crowded escalators. Escalators packed with anxious shoppers trying
to get to the big sale at Bath &AMP; Body Works. Escalators crammed
with annoying teens chatting away on their parents' cell phones
while munching on soft pretzels. Escalators jammed with elderly
mall walkers on their way to level two for a change of scenery.
Then, there's the most annoying aspect of holiday escalators: those
little punks (let loose by browsing parents) who insist on walking
down the ``up'' escalator. I know, this ritual is an age-old
holiday tradition, but tradition or not, it's totally annoying;
annoying enough to be declared Annoying Gadget of the Week.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
