<SLUG> BC-TECH-LINK21-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A few good Web sites
 &HT;    By Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ www.this.com _ If the idea of a ``safe''
Internet is about as appealing as a Stepford wives potluck,
this.com may not be the place for you. But if you're a parent and
you're worried about what your kids are viewing on the Internet
(and whether they've washed behind the ears), this.com provides
``filtered Internet access,'' the online equivalent of wearing a
condom. Links from this.com are guaranteed to be free of smut.
</P>
<P>
   www.thehungersite.com _ Feel like making a difference? Unlike
those annoying chain e-mails that promise to save a child's life if
you just forward a message to all your friends, this Web site
really does do charity work, and all it takes is a click from you.
At The Hunger Site, clicking a button will donate 1/4 cup of food
per sponsor to countries that need it. With the help of companies
such as Infospace, the click-through program is donating more than
50 tons of food a week to the United Nations World Food Program.
</P>
<P>
   www.selectsmart.com _ SelectSmart takes the pain and agony out
of life decisions. Can't decide for whom to vote next November? Use
the Presidential Candidate Selector to find the candidate who
matches your political views when you answer a list of questions.
Want the best wine for an upcoming dinner? Answer the questions and
it'll match you with a suitable vintage. And best of all, you can
get your palm read by matching your hand with illustrations of palm
lines. A lifesaver for the indecisive.
</P>
<P>
   www.obitdetails.com _ It's never too late to think about death
(unless you're dead, of course), and if you're in a morbid mood, or
just want to honor a dead person you know, hop on to
obitdetails.com, an obituary listing site. For a one-time fee of
$145, you can post a lasting obituary that includes sound and video
clips. As the company says in its press mailing, ``Who cares if
you're not a celebrity? No matter your notoriety, everyone deserves
to be remembered.'' For those of who don't leave much of a legacy
behind, here's hoping somebody will be willing to bookmark us.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
