 &HT;    Operating without a Net
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ With the battle for mobile phones that include
wireless Internet access heating up, PrimeCo's latest consumer
model, the PCX-3500XL ($159 after rebate, www.primeco.com) is
curiously absent of Web access features. The company admits it's a
few months behind on the technology being rolled out by Sprint PCS.
What the 3500XL, a titanium gray flip phone made by Audiovox, does
have is a sleek feel at a feather-light 4.4 ounces, a hands-free
kit, editable phone rings and enough battery lifefor 120 minutes of
talk time.
</P>
