r l BC-WIRELESS-MOUSE21-COX     12-20 0381
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WIRELESS-MOUSE21-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Graphire mouse is fit and functional
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The mouses _ or is it mice? _ that come with computers are
functional, but they can have problems.
</P>
<P>
   The cord gets tangled, the little rolling ball gets gummed up
and stops working smoothly and a mouse isn't a good tool for
drawing.
</P>
<P>
   Wacom Technology Corp. of Vancouver, British Columbia, is
marketing an inexpensive cordless mouse and pen set that gets
around those problems. The Graphire cordless system sells for about
$100 and incorporates many of the features of Wacom's more
expensive tools for computer graphic artists.
</P>
<P>
   The system is only compatible with recent computer systems. It
operates with a personal computer with serial port on Windows 95 or
later or Windows 4.0 or later. The Graphire version with USB
connections requires Windows 98.
</P>
<P>
   For Macintoshes, an iMac with USB and Mac OS 8.5 or Power
Macintosh with USB port and Mac OS 8.0 or later are required.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of plugging the mouse into the computer as with a
regular setup, the mouse pad of the Graphire is connected. Because
the mouse pad doesn't move around much, the connecting cable
doesn't get tangled.
</P>
<P>
   The lightweight cordless mouse operates like any other mouse; as
you move it, the cursor on the screen moves. Wacom claims, though,
that the Graphire is two to three times more accurate than an
ordinary mouse.
</P>
<P>
   The Graphire mouse also comes with a scrolling wheel that allows
you to move documents up and down on the computer screen. It has an
extra button that can be programmed.
</P>
<P>
   The pen that comes with Graphire also can be used with word
processing programs, but it's most useful in graphics applications.
It can be used in painting, photo editing, writing text longhand or
anything else you might do with a pen or paintbrush.
</P>
<P>
   The software that comes with Graphire includes Painter Classic,
which is supposed to emulate traditional art tools such as chalks,
oil paints and more.
</P>
<P>
   The product is available online direct from Wacom. The company
said it is also available at Comp USA stores. For ordering
information visit www.wacom.com or call (800) 922-6613.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
