<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE HIGH-SPEED STYLE OF `RUN LOLA RUN' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Run Lola Run'' (DVD) _ This energetic, stylish
import is enhanced by the superior sound quality of the DVD format.
Lola runs and runs and runs. While the gimmick is that everything
happens in real time, the story is a solid crime melodrama and the
acting is first-rate.
</P>
<P>
   ``American Pie'' (DVD) _ It's easy to understand why kids went
for this sophomoric undertaking. It deals with first-time sex in a
completely unoriginal manner _ but doesn't every adolescent
thinking about sex believe that these feelings are unique and
unprecedented? And if you're not an adolescent, you must remember
the kid who sat in the back of the class telling dirty jokes _ they
weren't that funny, but you gave him credit for having the guts to
tell them.
</P>
<P>
   ``Summer of Sam'' _ Director Spike Lee tackles the story of
David Berkowitz, the ``Son of Sam' serial killer, from the point of
view of New York's neighborhoods in the late '70s. It's a risky
undertaking, but Lee manages to pull it off.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Adventures of Elmo in Grouchland'' _ Muppet-mania
continues with this delightful adventure with Elmo, a
long-neglected member of the Henson Company's household. Kids love
the little guy, and parents can learn a few things, too.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY GIFT: If you're looking for just one solid source book
for home video, check out ``Video Hound's Golden Movie Retriever
2000.'' For just $22, it includes more than 22,000 capsule reviews,
plus information about DVD availability and awards, not to mention
some great subgenre lists (including ``Oedipal Allegories'' and
``Shrinks''). The competition among video books is fierce _ Leonard
Maltin, American Movie Classics, Blockbuster, and the New York
Times all have guides _ but the Hound is rising to the occasion.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 28: ``Dudley Do-Right,'' ``Better than
Chocolate,'' ``Desert Blue'' (DVD). Jan. 4: ``The Thomas Crown
Affair'' (DVD), ``Sayonara,'' Jan. 11: ``The Art of Buster Keaton''
(DVD), ``The Extreme Adventures of Super Dave.'' Jan. 18: ``An
Ideal Husband,'' ``The Hitchhiker,'' ``From Dusk to Dawn 3,'' ``The
13th Warrior.'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan. 25: ``Runaway Bride,''
``My Life So Far,'' ``The Sex Monster,'' ``My Son the Fanatic,''
``The Tempest,'' ``Woman Wanted.'' Feb. 1: ``The Cabinet of Dr.
Caligari,'' ``Nosferatu.''
</P>
</TEXT>
