</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-POLITICS-ANALYSIS _ MOSCOW _ A senior Kemlin official
called Sunday's parliamentary election results a ``peaceful
revolution'' that offers new hope for Russia's long-stalled market
and democratic reforms. But nothing is a sure thing given Russia's
complex political system, the ongoing war in Chechnya and the
unpredictable President Boris Yeltsin. The results of Sunday's
election altered the political landscape in Russia more than anyone
could have imagined. But the pitfalls on the way to political unity
are many. (Holmes, Cox News Service)
</P>
