<P>
   TEX-TAX-DISCOUNT _ WASHINGTON _ For the owners of Austin's Texas
Discount Furniture, the cost of doing business could go up $2.4
million. That's how much the Internal Revenue Service is demanding
in back taxes and penalties from the owners, their son and his
wife, and their daughter and her husband. The IRS ruled they had
unreported gross receipts from Texas Discount and SDB Check
Cashing. (Moskal, Cox News Service)
</P>
