Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PRISON-DISTURBANCE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ State prison guards lost
control of a cellblock early Monday at a Beeville prison after the
doors of about 80 prison cells unexplicably opened early Monday.
Control was regained after several hours but officials are
perplexed about why the doors would open. The disturbance occurred
at the McConnell Unit, where a prison guard was stabbed to death
late last week. (Ward, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   BIG-MOON _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ In recognition of Western
civilization's frenzied quest to find a divine _ or, at least,
cosmic _ sign that the end of the millennium approaches, try this:
The Internet is alight with e-mails declaring that Wednesday
night's last full moon of the millennium will be the brightest
first night of winter in 133 years, perhaps portending disaster.
Most astronomers aren't impressed, saying the event isn't as big a
deal as millennium pundits claim. (O'Meilia, Palm Beach Post) MOVED
