<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-20 15:01 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4329 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r l BC-MILLENNIUM-PARTY-SIDE     12-20 0219
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MILLENNIUM-PARTY-SIDE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAKE IT A FAMILY AFFAIR
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Maybe champagne and caviar aren't your speed, and you'd rather
usher the old year out surrounded by your family in a quiet
celebration.
</P>
<P>
   For this very special New Year's Eve, Susan V. Bosak, author of
``Something to Remember Me By'' (The Communication Project;
$15.95), a storybook about keepsakes a grandmother gives her
granddaughter, has several suggestions for family get-togethers:
</P>
<P>
   _ Have a family scrapbook party, choosing favorite photos and
decorating themed pages.
</P>
<P>
   _ Read favorite stories out loud, tying stories to personal
memories and bringing them alive with old mementos like your
grandfather's watch or your grandmother's earrings.
</P>
<P>
   _ Have a ``best memory'' party, with each person telling their
favorite memories of other family members.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make a millennium time capsule to be stored and opened in five
years.
</P>
<P>
   If you'd like more party ideas, check out
!bold!www.ShindigZ.com!off! on the Internet, which bills itself as
the online party superstore. Not only does ShindigZ sell 8,000
party items, it also has a staff of party planners who'll help put
together your own personal shindig, free of charge. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-20-99 1501EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19991220.0141 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-20 15:02 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4332 &Cx1f; taf-z
u l BC-FASHION-NYT-BUDGET &LR;      12-20 0105
