   DOMINICAN-JEWS (Sosua, Dominican Republic) _ A famous outpost of
Holocaust-era Jews, accepted by the Dominican Republic when no
other country would save them from Hitler, has dwindled to the
point where services are said on an outdoor desk with lawn
furniture. By David Abel. 1250 words.
