<P>
   WORCESTER-HOMELESS (Worcester, Mass.) _ Though nearly two
decades apart in age, Julie Barnes, 19, and Tom Levesque, 37, had a
common background: troubled, broken families. They bonded and
forged a stormy relationship in shelters and vacant buildings. But
their fates became inextricably linked the night a candle fell over
inside the Worcester Cold Storage &AMP; Warehouse Co. By Joanna Weiss.
1800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; VETERINARY-HOLDUPS (Hudson, N.H.) _ An increase in armed
robberies at veterinary clinics is being spurred by the desire to
obtain Ketamine -- ``Special K'' on the street. Suddenly, working
at the local vet clinic is unpredictable as the overnight at the
7-11. By Lois Shea. 1100 words.
</P>
