<HEADLINE>
I WANT MY MTV ... TRIVIA
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   There are board games that let you buy and sell real estate,
spell words and look for murder clues. And now, from Cardinal
Industries Inc. and MTV: Music Television, there's MTV: The Game,
with 1,000 music trivia questions in a board game format.
</P>
<P>
   For the holiday season, the game comes packaged in a collector's
tin. Available at mass market merchandisers such as Target, Kmart
and Toys R Us, specialty stores and Internet Web sites including
www.amazon.com and www.e-toys.com, suggested retail price is
$19.99. &QL;
</P>
