<HEADLINE>
RICKY MARTIN ... ON A (KEY) CHAIN
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you're looking for a stocking stuffer for the music lover on
your Christmas list, Yaboom Ltd., a joint venture between Toymax
International Inc. and Street Life Ltd., has come up with Music on
the Go musical key chains.
</P>
<P>
   The palm-sized players, with attached key chain, play a full
song by an artist of your choice: Ricky Martin, Britney Spears, the
Backstreet Boys, TLC, Celine Dion, Cher, Shania Twain and 'N Sync.
Powered by three L1154 batteries (included), the key chains retail
for less than $15 at music and other stores. Although the company
raves about the sound quality of the tiny player, only a true lover
of the artist _ or a teen-ager _ probably will appreciate the tinny
tones. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
