its antioxidant properties, which researchers believe may help the
body fight everything from cancer to cataracts. (320 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Gay men are almost twice as likely to smoke cigarettes as men
over all, a new study finds. The study was done by researchers at
the University of California at San Francisco, and looked at 2,600
men who described themselves as gay or bisexual. About 48 percent
reported smoking, compared with about 27 percent of all American
men. (200 words)
</P>
