<HEADLINE>
Y2K IN THE BLINK OF AN EYE
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   You've bought the mug, you've got the T-shirt, so what's next as
a tangible sign that you're ready to usher in the year 2000? How
about what Wesley Jessen, makers of WildEyes novelty contact
lenses, calls a way to ``scream with your mouth shut with 2000
literally written across your eyes''?
</P>
<P>
   Year 2000 Contact Lenses have a clear pupil (so they won't
obscure your vision) surrounded by an iris that's champagne yellow,
emblazoned with the number 2000, flanked by confetti and streamers.
(If you're not up for that, there's always the firm's ``bloodshot''
contact lenses, suitable for millennium party wear.)
</P>
<P>
   The celebratory eye wear is available in most common
prescriptions at about $99 per pair, excluding professional fees,
can be prescribed by optometrists, opticians, ophthalmologists or
retail optical chains. For more information or to locate an eye
care professional to prescribe the lenses, visit
www.wild-eyes.com. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
