<HEADLINE>
TEN ... NINE ... EIGHT ... HOW TV'S BIGGEST STARS WILL SPEND NEW
YEAR'S EVE 
</HEADLINE>
  (This ``separate buy'' article is from this week's StarBeat
entertainment package.) 
 (To publish this article, it must be purchased _ the rate is not
prohibitive _ from New York Times Syndicate sales representative
DEBRA WEYDERT at 732-390-4480, or by fax at 732-390-4697.) 
 (She also has information on how to subscribe to StarBeat, a weekly
package of five intriguing features with color art.) 
 (Includes a color slide of David Hyde Pierce and Jane Leeves in a
scene from ``Frasier.'') 
 c.1999 TV Guide Canada  
 Not to be released in Canada until December 28. 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Say, Mr. or Ms. Television Star, where do you plan to be when
the ball drops on Dec. 31? &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Charisma Carpenter of ``Angel'': ``My mom is getting married, so
I'm going to be traveling. I was really trying to spend time in my
new house with my family, but it looks like the family is going to
be traveling to be with her on her happy day.''
</P>
<P>
   Sarah Michelle Gellar of ``Buffy the Vampire Slayer'': ``I'll be
in Australia with some friends, doing who knows what.''
</P>
<P>
   Mandy Patinkin of ``Chicago Hope'': ``I have a job singing at a
private party on Maui.''
</P>
<P>
   Jon Stewart of ``The Daily Show'': ``All the computers are going
to crash, and we'll have to go back to living like we did in, like,
1980. I liked 1980.''
</P>
<P>
   James Van Der Beek of ``Dawson's Creek'': ``I am so far behind,
and I probably should start planning something. I mean, every
flight is booked, so I don't know where I'll be.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant Gumbel of ``The Early Show'': ``I've been invited to
spend it on top of a mountain in Vail. I think instead I'll spend
it at home.''
</P>
<P>
   Patricia Heaton of ``Everybody Loves Raymond'': ``We're going to
(producer) Phil Rosenthal's house. If Jesus Christ is coming back,
it's going to be at Phil's.''
</P>
<P>
   Phil Rosenthal, creator of ``Everybody Loves Raymond'': ``I
didn't invite Jesus. I'll put him on the list. I decided the only
way I didn't have to go out was if I had a party. I've never had a
big party, so we're doing it.''
</P>
<P>
   Jane Leeves of ``Frasier'': ``I just want to be with certain
people _ my husband, my mom and dad, my sisters and brothers.
That's the most important thing to me.''
</P>
<P>
   David Hyde Pierce of ``Frasier'': ``I've talked with friends,
and I've decided it would be a good idea to not be out traveling,
not on a boat crossing the international dateline and not be in
Times Square with every other person in New York. I might change my
mind, but it's more relaxing at home. I also think the whole
millennium thing will make a good story line for `Frasier' _ we
should get some mileage out of that.''
</P>
<P>
   Courteney Cox of ``Friends'': ``I'd really like to spend it with
really close friends _ I really don't need to do some big blowout
party.''
</P>
<P>
   Matthew Perry of ``Friends'': ``Hopefully I won't be in a plane.
I'm not sure exactly what I'm going to be doing _ all New Year's
Eves are anticlimactic, this may be the most of all. Hopefully I'll
think of something fun to do.''
</P>
<P>
   David Schwimmer of ``Friends'': ``I'm going out of town with
friends.''
</P>
<P>
   David James Elliott of ``JAG'': ``We're not going anywhere. I
don't want to be traveling.''
</P>
<P>
   Kathie Lee Gifford of ``Live With Regis and Kathie Lee'': ``I'll
be in the Florida keys with my family, doing as little as
possible.''
</P>
<P>
   Sammo Hung of ``Martial Law'': ``I hope everything in the world
is the best. I really hope for ... world peace. I really hope, you
know?''
</P>
<P>
   Brandy of ``Moesha'': ``I really want to take it easy and be
with my family _ that's the most important thing.''
</P>
<P>
   Joe Rogan of ``NewsRadio'': ``It's the end of the world! People
are going to eat other people! I'm going to be in the mountains. I
got two pit bulls and a lot of guns _ I'm locking down, dude!''
</P>
<P>
   Patty Duke of ``The Patty Duke Show'': ``I would like to go to
church. I haven't been in a long time, and I've sort of decided
that the nature and trees and sky where I live in Idaho are my
church. But there's a part of me that misses the tradition, and I
would like that to be part of my moving into the next millennium.''
</P>
<P>
   Camryn Manheim of ``The Practice'': ``I have a longstanding
commitment to be with my bridge club. I will be in New York on the
Lower East Side, playing duplicate bridge.''
</P>
<P>
   Rosie O'Donnell of ``Rosie'': ``I'll be down at my house in
Miami. And I thought it'd be neat right at the stroke of midnight
to take my kids' picture _ then I can say, `That's where you were
at the turn of the century.'''
</P>
<P>
   Katherine Heigl of ``Roswell'': ``I want to go on a cruise to
Greece, but now I'm afraid it's too late and I'm going to end up
watching TV. I'll be on my couch in my living room.''
</P>
<P>
   Melissa Joan Hart of ``Sabrina the Teen-Age Witch'': ``I was
going to have a big party, and then I decided I'll just go to New
York and go to someone else's party. Now I'm having a party again,
so we'll see what happens.''
</P>
<P>
   Molly Shannon of ``Saturday Night Live'': ``Drew Barrymore's
invited me to a party in L.A., at her house. Doesn't that sound
nice?''
</P>
<P>
   Kathy Griffin of ``Suddenly Susan'': ``I'm going to be on my
roof with a shotgun, because I am terrified of this Y2K business
and I'm just gonna pick off looters. So stay out of my
neighborhood.''
</P>
<P>
   Brooke Shields of ``Suddenly Susan'': ``I was thinking of going
to Israel. I have been there before, and I think it would be
phenomenal to do that. I can't wait _ I mean, what a pure time, you
know?''
</P>
<P>
   Ashton Kutcher of ``That '70s Show'': ``I don't want to be in a
big city, so I'm going to Wisconsin, out in the middle of nowhere,
to snowmobile around a lake.''
</P>
<P>
   John Lithgow of ``Third Rock From the Sun'': ``We're trying to
keep it ordinary and spend New Year's all by ourselves, just the
family in our little cabin in Montana.''
</P>
<P>
   Suzanne Somers of ``Three's Company'' and ``Candid Camera'':
``At the moment, I think we're staying home. But I'm hoping Merv
Griffin throws a party _ he gives great parties. Let's start that
rumor, and maybe he'll end up giving one.''
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Love Hewitt of ``Time of Your Life'': ``I'm staying at
home in my PJs and curling up with a good book and a cup of hot
chocolate. I really don't want to be involved in all the madness.''
</P>
<P>
   Al Roker of ``Today'': ``I'm going to Disney World! My wife,
Deborah Roberts, is part of that huge ABC 27-hour extravaganza, so
I will be following her and bringing the baby and my daughter
Courtney, and taking a friend.''
</P>
<P>
   Kathy Najimy of ``Veronica's Closet'': ``I want to go to some
place like Kansas, sit in the middle of a field with my daughter
and my husband, and pray nothing falls on us. Actually, I'll
probably just stay home and have a party.''
</P>
<P>
   Star Jones of ``The View'': ``I plan on making love to my
husband. And I'm not married.''
</P>
<P>
   Tim Matheson of ``The West Wing'': ``My birthday is Dec. 31. I'm
trying to get out of all engagements to be with my wife and three
kids. It's something I want them to remember, so I'm trying to plan
an agenda that would encompass all of us.''
</P>
<P>
   Eric McCormack of ``Will &AMP; Grace'': ``I'm reading too many scary
things, like you shouldn't be flying, you shouldn't be in an
elevator. I want to be close to home, I think, something
intimate.''
</P>
<P>
   Vince McMahon of the World Wrestling Federation: ``There are
going to be so many things going on New Year's Eve, I'll probably
do something special the day before or the day after.''
</P>
<P>
   Gillian Anderson of ``The X-Files'': ``I'm really freaked about
the Y2K thing, so it'll be something that doesn't involve
technology.'' &QL; 
