<P>
   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BURLINGTON-CANADIAN (Undated) _ Burlington Northern Santa Fe
Corp. and the Canadian National Railway Co. announced a $6 billion
merger Monday that would create the largest railroad in North
America. The combined railroa would have 50,000 miles of track
stretching from Halifax to the Gulf of Mexico, connecting every
state west of the Mississippi and every major city across the
length of Canada. Burlington Northern, a longtime advocate of a
transcontinental railroad, would vault ahead of Union Pacific as
the biggest railroad and solidify its position as the largest
carrier of coal and grain. By Charles V. Bagli.
