semiconductors, they are loaded with bits of actual DNA that make
up genes or fragments of genes. Biochips will bring genomics, the
study of all the genes in a living organism, out of the research
laboratory and into the daily practice of medicine. If genomics
delivers on its promise, health care will shift from a focus on
detection and treatment to a process of prediction and prevention.
